<item>
            <title>[LU-19017] osd-ldiskfs osd_stats_init() incorrectly refers to zfs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19017</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lustre/osd-ldiskfs/osd_lproc.c::osd_stats_init() has this seemingly copy paste bit:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;static int osd_stats_init(struct osd_device *osd)
{
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; char param[MAX_OBD_NAME * 4];
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; int result = -ENOMEM;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ENTRY;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; scnprintf(param, sizeof(param), &quot;osd-zfs.%s.stats&quot;, osd_name(osd));
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; osd-&amp;gt;od_stats = ldebugfs_stats_alloc(LPROC_OSD_LAST, param,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;osd-&amp;gt;od_dt_dev.dd_debugfs_entry,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;0);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not sure I see it actually printed anywhere though.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Recently introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57305&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57305&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
